      "args": {
        "narrative": "The analysis began with a base Black-Litterman scenario that showed a portfolio with a Sharpe ratio of 0.2353, constrained by a maximum weight of 40% per asset. The top weights were JPM (40%), AAPL (33.36%), and AMZN (22.96%).\n\nThe view importance test identified \"Strong earnings report for Microsoft\" and \"TSLA underperform JPM\" as the most impactful views, with significant allocation shifts when removed. The fragility scan on these views showed that the portfolio is particularly sensitive to the \"TSLA underperform JPM\" view, with Sharpe ratios increasing significantly as the magnitude of this view increased.\n\nThe allocation envelope analysis revealed that the most stable allocation across scenarios was for JPM, consistently at 40%. However, TSLA showed a wide range of allocation from 2.75% to 16.83%, indicating sensitivity to the views tested.\n\nGiven the goal of finding a robust allocation with a maximum of 40% per position, the scenario with the highest Sharpe ratio (0.4044) was achieved with the \"TSLA underperform JPM\" view at a magnitude of 0.7. This scenario also maintained the constraint of no more than 40% per asset.\n\nRecommended weights for a robust allocation are:\n- AAPL: 38.7%\n- MSFT: 5.77%\n- AMZN: 9.78%\n- TSLA: 40%\n- JPM: 5.74%",
        "risk_flags": [
